description.narrative: Strengthened capacities of government authorities for delivery of early childhood and basic education for children in BARMM, which contributes to Adolescent Empowerment, Cross-Sectoral Communication For Development, Cross-Sectoral Monitoring, Data And Situation Analyses, Early Childhood Development, Equitable Access To Quality Education, Learning Outcomes, Sanitation, Skills Development, Skills Development (Covid), Water. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Advocacy And Public Engagement, Developing And Leveraging Resources And Partnerships, Evaluations, Research And Data, Fostering Innovation And Use Of New Technologies, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: By 2023, more children and adolescents, especially the most disadvantaged, have improved education and learning outcomes.

title.narrative: Strengthened capacities of government authorities for delivery of early childhood and basic education for children in BARMM

description.narrative: In target municipalities coverage of early learning increased significantly from 40% in 2018 to 49%, due to setting up of new early learning centres in Madrassah schools, however no progress was made to expand coverage of elementary services nor alternative learning services reflecting the weak capacities of the education system to respond and need for a much greater concerted effort. The transition from a regional administration to a new devolved Bangsamoro Government (February 2019) and setting up of a new Ministry of Education was the major constraint to progress. UNICEF has created a strong relationship and partnership with the Ministry | Status:Constrained | As-of Date:07/02/2020
